text: Toms River, New Jersey is a township in the U.S. state of New Jersey. It is the county seat of Ocean County. Toms River was originally known as Dover Township. It was called Toms River so much that they voted to officially change the name of the town on November 7, 2006. ==References== Category:Townships in New Jersey Category:County seats in New Jersey Category:Ocean County, New Jersey
title: Toms River, New Jersey
